@startuml API-001
!pragma layout smetana
title API-001 v1.0 — Runtime contract groups and implementation owners
top to bottom direction
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #F6F8FB
  BorderColor #174F63
  FontColor #172033
  RoundCorner 12
}

rectangle "WorkspaceShell\nclient orchestration" as Client #EAF4EF
rectangle "Analysis contracts\nPOST /api/analyze\nGET/POST /api/analysis-runs\nGET/POST /api/ai/decision-score" as Analysis
rectangle "Context and lineage contracts\nPOST /api/context/market · GET /api/context/*\nGET /api/source-lineage\nGET /api/data-sources/readiness" as Context
rectangle "Project and evidence contracts\nGET/POST /api/projects · /api/aois · /api/reports\nGET/POST /api/report-packages · /api/validation/*" as Evidence
rectangle "Control-plane contracts\nGET /api/health · /api/db/health\nGET /api/platform/activation-status\nGET /api/pilot-backend/status\nGET /api/security/rls-readiness" as Control #FFF9EC

Client -down-> Analysis : analysis request/result
Client -down-> Context : context and source basis
Client -down-> Evidence : project, persistence and export
Evidence -down-> Control : runtime capability is checked separately
Context -[hidden]down-> Evidence
Analysis -[hidden]down-> Context

note bottom of Control
Route existence is not an activation claim. Each handler may report local fallback,
not-configured or blocked readiness states and must preserve the required caveat.
end note
@enduml
